### AI - extract problem info from screenshots
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/extract
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "images": [
    "data:image/png;base64,{{imageBase64}}"
  ],
  "language": "python",
  "provider": "openai",
  "extractionModel": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "conversationContext": "Solve this coding problem step by step."
}

### AI - solve a problem
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/solve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "problemInfo": {
    "problem_statement": "Given two integers a and b, return their sum.",
    "constraints": "-10^9 <= a, b <= 10^9",
    "example_input": "2 3",
    "example_output": "5"
  },
  "language": "python",
  "provider": "openai",
  "solutionModel": "gpt-4o-mini"
}

### AI - process (extract + solve in one call)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/process
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "images": [
    "data:image/png;base64,{{imageBase64}}"
  ],
  "language": "python",
  "provider": "openai",
  "extractionModel": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "solutionModel": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "conversationContext": "Provide a concise explanation."
}

### AI - debug a solution from screenshots
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/debug
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "images": [
    "data:image/png;base64,{{imageBase64}}"
  ],
  "problemStatement": "The code returns wrong output for large input.",
  "language": "python",
  "provider": "openai",
  "debuggingModel": "gpt-4o-mini"
}

### AI - transcribe audio
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/transcribe
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "audio": "REPLACE_WITH_BASE64_AUDIO",
  "mimeType": "audio/webm",
  "provider": "openai",
  "speechRecognitionModel": "whisper-1"
}

### AI - answer suggestions for interview questions
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/answer-suggestions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Tell me about a time you handled pressure.",
  "conversationHistory": "Candidate discussed teamwork and deadlines.",
  "screenshotContext": "Resume screenshot attached.",
  "candidateProfile": {
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "resume": "Frontend engineer with 3 years of experience.",
    "jobDescription": "Looking for a React engineer."
  },
  "provider": "openai",
  "answerModel": "gpt-4o-mini"
}

### AI - get usage summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/usage
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



### POST /api/ai/extract — upload real image files (multipart, new behaviour)
# VS Code REST Client sends each file part as multipart/form-data.
# The server converts them to base64 internally — no change needed in your client.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/extract/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="screenshot.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./image.png
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="language"

python
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="provider"

openai
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="extractionModel"

gpt-4o-mini
------Boundary--





### AI - Solve quiz from uploaded image
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/quiz/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="quiz.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./image.png
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="provider"

openai
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="extractionModel"

gpt-5.5
------Boundary--

### AI - Solve quiz using base64 JSON
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "images": ["data:image/png;base64,{{imageBase64}}"],
  "provider": "openai",
  "extractionModel": "gpt-5.5"
}



